  @Description_8b403d4f = N'Real-time agent type — a first-class peer of Loop and Flow that drives a streaming, full-duplex BaseRealtimeModel session (voice today, video later) instead of an iterative reasoning loop. The model owns the listen-reason-speak loop; the agent delegates real work back to async (Loop/Flow) agents via tool calls. The first agent of this type is the Voice Co-Agent, which voices on behalf of any target agent. The system prompt is per-agent (assembled at session start), so there is no type-level SystemPromptID.'
